      \field{annotation}{REVIEW : This paper tackles the highly combinatorial Nurse Rostering Problem (NRP) by modeling it as a Weighted Constraint Satisfaction Proble. In staff scheduling, standard binary constraints are often insufficient to concisely express complex labor rules. To overcome this, the authors introduce soft global constraints (specifically, the Soft Regular and Soft Global Cardinality constraints) directly into the TOULBAR2 solver. By developing specialized flow-based and dynamic programming algorithms to enforce soft local consistencies (like EDAC) inside these global constraints, TOULBAR2 successfully computes optimal schedules that balance strict hospital coverage requirements with nurses' personal preferences. OVERVIEW : L'élaboration des emplois du temps du personnel est prb classique et difficile en RO. Cet article est crucial car il explique une évolution majeure de TOULBAR2 : l'ajout de contraintes globales souples. Cela permet d'expliquer que pour planifier des ressources efficacement, les algorithmes de base (OSAC/VAC sur des contraintes binaires) ont dû être adaptés pour traiter des contraintes "globales" (qui touchent beaucoup de variables en même temps).}
